            "contents": "<p><strong>Whoare we?</strong><br><br>We at Siemens Healthineers™ are committed to helping healthcare providersglobally to succeed in today's dynamic environment. We are encouraged totransform the way things are done - because we want what is best for ourpeople, our customers and ultimately the health of mankind.<br><br>While we are invested in engineering perfection - leading-edge medicaltechnologies and services, we don't stop there. We're also deeply invested inour 46.000 people with the hearts of pioneers and minds of engineers, highlycommitted and connected in this industry. And as we strive to craft the futureof healthcare, our overall success will depend on our ability to continuouslyreinvent ourselves.<br><br>Responsibilities:<br><br>•   Provide onsite clinicalapplications' training to user's equipment in CT modality area.<br><br>•   Provide ongoing applications supportas the customer's trusted advisor throughout the equipment lifecycle to achievecustomer's desired outcomes<br><br>•   Maintaining satisfactory after-salerelationships and development of long-term customer relationships coupled withthe ability to identify and capitalize on opportunities that immediatelysatisfy customer needs.<br><br>•   Continuously develop and improve anetwork of key opinion leaders within the CT customers.<br><br>•   Show the outstanding differentiatorsthat are in the configuration of the system sold based on customer's clinicalneeds.<br><br>•   Support Trade show/Workshops/showsites/Customer visits.<br><br>•   Adopt the digital transformation ofapplication trainings as per company trend and implement the blended training.<br><br>•   Supporting the sales team withtechnical/clinical expertise if required.<br><br>Required Experience:<br><br>•   Graduate of higher education withstudies in the field of medicine, bioengineering, medical physics or graduatenurse programs are an advantage <br><br>•   Demonstrated experience scanning on SiemensCT systems is an advantage.<br><br>•   Minimum 2-3 years of CTtechnical/clinical experience.<br><br>•   Deep understanding of CT clinicaleducation training and associated process implementation.<br><br>•   Good communication and presentationskills.<br><br>•   Deep knowledge of CT Physics <br><br>•   Required to travel up to 40% withinthe country via all available modes of transportation.<br><br>•   Advanced English<br><br>•   Excellent social skills including,team working skills and good interpersonal skills.<br><br>•   Proficient use of softwareapplications such as Outlook, Word, PowerPoint, Excel.<br><br>•   Self-motivated, willingness to takethe initiative and to improve.<br><br>•   Willingness to be flexible/adapt tochanging work environments.<br><br>•   Driver's license<br><br>Develop training plans and managethe training process for Radiologists, physicists, and technologists to ensuretechnical competence and proper operation of Siemens CT equipment. Consult withdepartment staff regarding best practices such as workflow, image acquisition,protocol optimization, and image quality. Drive customer satisfaction for SiemensCT products.<br><br>SiemensHealthineers stands for culture diversity and inclusion. Check for yourself byapplying for our position and let us prove to you that we do what we say!<br><br><b>Organization:</b> Siemens Healthineers<br><br><b>Company:</b> Siemens Healthcare S.R.L.<br><br><b>Experience Level:</b> Experienced Professional<br><br><b>Job Type:</b> Full-time</p>",
