            "contents": "<p>At Lisbon Tech Hub we create valuein the digital transition of companies from Portugal to the world. There are morethan 1200 professionals working in Cybersecurity, Analytics BusinessIntelligence, Application Lifecycle Management, IT Project &amp; ServiceManagement and IT Infrastructure Management. Check it out: www.siemens.pt/lxtechhub<br><br>We are a global powerhouse focusing on the areas ofelectrification, automation, and digitalization. One of the world's largestproducers of energy-efficient, resource-saving technologies, Siemens is aleading supplier of systems for power generation and transmission as well asmedical diagnosis. In infrastructure and industry solutions the company plays agroundbreaking role.<br><br>Looking for a chance to create a positive impact on oursociety? Join us!<br> What rolewill you play? <br>Rethinking IT.<br><br>We have lots of ideas about how to successfullydrive digitalization in companies. For example, with open cloud platforms,highly developed security systems, and clever tools for developers. What isyour role in this? Move the world from behind the scenes with your IT expertiseand passion for game-changing information technology. Rethink IT and steerprojects in completely new directions. Be bold when others would have given up.In short, play a key role in driving digitalization forward! We'll provide theresources you need to do this. We also offer a variety of opportunities to getinvolved and to be part of a global network of IT experts and professionals.Welcome to our world! <br><br><strong>Vision</strong>:<br><br>Leverage the full potential of the ITorganization, people and processes in line with the Company priorities &amp; ITStrategic Framework.<br><br><strong>Mission</strong>:<br><br>We enable a learning and adaptive organizationfitting the needs of a changing environment &amp; digitalization, empoweredemployees, effective communication and an efficient process and tools landscape.<br><br>We make real what matters. This is your role asa member of the organization, transformation, people and communications team. <br><br><strong>Using your expertise, you will be responsiblefor:</strong><br><br><ul><li>•   Driving the organizational designfor agile &amp; digital transformation / culture and organizational learning</li><li>•  Implementingand improving the Operating &amp; Collaboration Model to achieve thetransformation goals</li><li>•  Deriveand implement corresponding transformation &amp; change activities,tools/methods</li></ul> We are looking for: <ul><li>High passion, positive energy, driveand can-do-attitude</li><li>Ability to quickly embrace thestrategic level and translate into consistent roadmap/measures for tangible&amp; sustainable outcomes</li><li>Team player with high empathy andintegrity</li><li>Confident presence &amp; assertiveness,pragmatism &amp; implementation strength</li><li>Flexibility to think &amp; act incomplex environments with high speed of change</li><li>Excellent communication (English) onall levels of an international organization</li><li>Strong consulting and collaborationskills </li><li>Master's degree in IT or businessadministration with focus on IT or similar degree</li><li>In-depth expertise in organizationaldesign, transformation &amp; change management projects &amp; tools</li><li>Leadership experience in largeinternational IT organizations or technology firms</li><li>Experience in leading of largeinternational transformation projects</li><li>German language is a plus</li></ul> What we have to offer:  A flexiblehome office and schedule policy, virtual budget to improve your home officesetup, health insurance, a Pension Plan and a Siemens Share Program time andfinancial support to your studies, medical center in the facilities, sportgroups, 2 days for volunteering initiatives and a cool and relaxed environment.  Access toe-learning platforms (Learnlight, Linkedin Learning and more), discounts withpartners.  #Siemens #LXTechHub#ITMakesUsMove <br>We recognize that building a diverse workforce is crucialto the success of our business. Therefore, Siemens provides equal employmentopportunities to all qualified individuals without regard to race, creed,color, religion, national origin, age, gender, marital status, sexual orientation,or non-disqualifying physical or mental handicap or disability.<br><br>We strongly encourage applications from a diverse talentpool and welcome the opportunity to discuss workplace adjustments with all ourapplicants to develop agile working and innovation.<br><br><b>Organization:</b> Information Technology<br><br><b>Company:</b> Siemens S.A.<br><br><b>Experience Level:</b> Experienced Professional<br><br><b>Job Type:</b> Full-time</p>",
